content:
The ADDDAY function of the Set Value element currently adds specified number of days to a date and returns the sum without considering the user's time zone. In Spring '25, the ADDDAY function will return the date after considering the time zone.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Experience Cloud sites in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions where OmniStudio is enabled.

Who: This change impacts OmniStudio customers who use the standard runtime and have disabled the Managed Package Runtime setting.

The input for the ADDDAY function is first converted to the user's time zone. In this example, the output of the ADDDAY function after adding 21 days to the input date is "2023-10-24".
title: Change in ADDDAY Function Output
